                <note>
                    <para>Closer adjustment can be made by working next thinner spacer to desired thickness using emery
                        cloth on a flat surface.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Wash spacer thoroughly of emery cuttings before installing on pinion.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After proper preload is achieved, remove end yoke, and install new seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200933">Figure 33</hotlnk>). Apply small amount of light grease on lip of sealing
                surface prior to installation (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200934">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200933" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200933" filename="../figg02/g0200933.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Install New Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0200934" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200934" filename="../figg02/g0200934.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Apply Light Grease on Sealing Surface</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install end yoke, washer, and pinion nut. Tighten to 325 ft-lbs. (440 Nm).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pinion gear and cage assembly are now ready to be installed into the carrier housing.</para>
